10.   COMMITMENTS AND CONTINGENCIES

AT

JANUARY 28, 2007, THE COMPANY WAS CONTINGENTLY LIABLE FOR APPROXIMATELY $1.2 BILLION UNDER OUTSTANDING LETTERS OF CREDIT ISSUED FOR CERTAIN BUSINESS TRANSACTIONS, INCLUDING INSURANCE

PROGRAMS, TRADE AND CONSTRUCTION CONTRACTS. THE COMPANY'S LETTERS OF CREDIT ARE PRIMARILY PERFORMANCE-BASED AND ARE NOT BASED ON CHANGES IN VARIABLE COMPONENTS, A LIABILITY OR AN EQUITY SECURITY OF

THE OTHER PARTY.

THE

COMPANY IS INVOLVED IN LITIGATION ARISING FROM THE NORMAL COURSE OF BUSINESS AND IN CERTAIN SECURITIES AND DERIVATIVE LITIGATION MATTERS. IN MANAGEMENT'S OPINION, THIS LITIGATION IS NOT EXPECTED

TO HAVE A MATERIAL ADVERSE EFFECT ON THE COMPANY'S CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL CONDITION OR RESULTS OF OPERATIONS.

